	(1264,288,'section_six_title','ICARUS COUNTER DRONE (UAV) SYSTEM'),
	(1265,288,'_section_six_title','field_5be88325f9007'),
	(1266,288,'section_six_body','<strong>Product Overview</strong>\r\n\r\n‘Icarus’ was designed and developed for current and emerging threats from Wi-Fi controlled drones (UAV’s) on both 2GHz and 5GHz unlicensed frequency bands.\r\n\r\n‘Icarus’ allows the operator to control drone activity whilst offering no threat to bona fide WIFI activity, through operation of a unique threat filter. Drones can be categorized as authorised, which means that non-threatening drone activity can be allowed, whilst unauthorised activity will be disrupted.\r\n\r\nWhen an unauthorised-drone flies within range of ‘Icarus’ the pilot loses both control of the drone and the video signal. The drone enters its safe mode and will hover briefly before returning to its take off coordinates. Unlike other systems ‘Icarus’ is not a frequency jammer.\r\n\r\n<strong>Whatever the threat, ICARUS is the answer.</strong>'),
