	(1378,350,'_section_two_subtitle','field_5be9c7e026d96'),
	(1379,350,'section_two_body','SIS services incorporate all the aspects, that you, as a client need to consider, ensuring the security and safety of you, your business, your staff and your confidential data. The other important considerations are of course business continuation and crisis management in the event of an unforeseen incident or disruption to your business or staff from whatever quarter that may come from.\r\n\r\nFrom the outset SIS will conduct an audit and risk assessment of all of your current security and fire prevention measures together with those crisis management and business continuation strategies you may have in place.\r\n\r\nHighly experienced investigators are specialists in their respective fields ensuring you have the full technical and business knowledge available to you on which to base your future security strategies will carry out this audit.\r\n\r\nOnce completed, we will work with you and your management team, in consultation with other key staff to plan and design strategies which are effective, workable and which everyone within the business understands, and the reasons why.\r\n\r\nEnsuring your cyber security involves a full understanding of the effective measures available to ensure data is properly protected at all times and fully backed up. It should be quickly recoverable in the event of a cyber-attack or other unforeseen cause. Unless effective measures are in place cyber-attacks can easily cripple your company and cost millions of pounds to recover. This applies equally to multinational organisations and to small and medium sized businesses (SME).\r\n\r\nWe, at SIS are not constrained by having to recommend any particular service providers when discussing physical security including building security, cyber security access control, perimeter security, fire prevention and detection.'),
